# Project: zahokejemdosvycar.cz

## Stack
- Next.js 14+ (App Router, TypeScript)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, @supabase/ssr)
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons

## Architecture Rules
- Use App Router (src/app/) with server components by default
- Minimize 'use client' — only for interactive components (forms, seat map, animations)
- Use server actions or API routes for data mutations
- All Supabase client creation via @supabase/ssr (NEVER use auth-helpers-nextjs)
- Use getAll/setAll for cookies (NEVER get/set/remove)

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Functional components only, no classes
- Use early returns for error handling
- Czech language for all UI text, English for code (variable names, comments)
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components

## Design System
- Colors: primary #C8102E (Kaufland red), secondary #003DA5 (hockey blue), accent #FFD700 (gold), bg #E8ECF0 (light gray) to #FFFFFF (white), text-primary #1A1A2E (dark), text-secondary #6B7280 (gray)
- Visual style: clean, illustrative, airy — light backgrounds, decorative clouds/mountains as SVG/CSS, flat/semi-flat design
- NO dark/techy look — inspired by the hero plane illustration (light gray sky, white clouds, Swiss mountains)
- Mobile first responsive design
- Min touch target 44x44px
- Font size min 16px for body

## Critical Business Logic
- Prize is determined by CODE, not by seat selection
- Seat selection is purely visual/UX
- One email = one registration (unique constraint)
- Only correct answers to the quiz question proceed to registration
- Codes are pre-generated with assigned prize types

## Performance
- Target < 3s load on 4G
- Optimize images with next/image
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components (SeatMap)
- Lazy load below-fold content

## Don'ts
- Don't over-engineer — this is a campaign microsite with limited lifespan
- Don't add unnecessary dependencies
- Don't create README or documentation unless asked
- Don't modify files unrelated to the current task
